<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFB7EF74FF42F9A7FDF8F921" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42F9A7FC94F9CD" blockId="31.[151,1437,1482,1689]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42F9A7FEE7F994" bold="true" box="[199,338,1554,1580]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Comments:</emphasis>
This is the first record of the species after its original description. This species also presents the lateral of the head white, as in 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB7EF74FE6EF982FDF1F9E9" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[491,580,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Philophyllia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latior">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FE6EF982FDF1F9E9" box="[491,580,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">P. latior</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the white stripe reaching the anterior coxae. 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB7EF74FBF2F982FAE3F9E8" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[1143,1366,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Philophyllia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venosa">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FBF2F982FAE3F9E8" box="[1143,1366,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Philophyllia venosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, presents a conspicuous yellow stain behind the eyes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42F9CBFDF8F921" blockId="31.[151,1437,1482,1689]" box="[199,589,1662,1689]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42F9CBFEEEF920" bold="true" box="[199,347,1662,1688]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
